\begin_layout Itemize
A threshold 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{T}$
\end_inset

 can be defined as the voltage at which the slope of the 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

-
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 curves vanishes which is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\psi'(V_{T})=g_{L}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
This is also the largest steady voltage at which the neuron can be maintained
 by a constant input current 
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

