Proof 
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Take the derivative of the r.h.s.
 of 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
C\frac{dV}{dt}=-g_{L}(V-V_{L})+\psi(V)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
and look for the zero 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\frac{d}{dV}\left[-g_{L}(V-V_{L})+\psi(V)\right] & =0\\
\psi'(V) & =g_{L}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
This is the point where the derivative changes its sign.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The corresponding current 
\begin_inset Formula $I_{T}=g_{L}(V_{T}-V_{L})-\psi(V_{T})$
\end_inset

 is the threshold current above which tonic firing occurs.
 
