status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Proof 
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
What is the 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

-
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 curve? If we apply a constant current 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

, we want to now at which value the membrane potential will settle? To answer
 this, we start from 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
C\frac{dV}{dt}=-g_{L}(V-V_{L})+\psi(V)+I
\]

\end_inset

and set the derivative on the l.h.s.
 to zero 
